@29 = ~Mask of the Skull

This ivory mask has been fashioned into the likeness of a human skull. Once per day the mask can be loosed to fly from the wearer’s face. It travels up to 50 feet away from the wearer and attacks a target assigned to it. The grinning skull mask makes a touch attack against the target. If it succeeds, the target must make a Fortitude saving throw (DC 20) or be struck dead, as if affected by a finger of death spell. If the target succeeds at his saving throw, he nevertheless takes 3d6+13 points of Dégâts . After attacking (whether successful or not), the mask flies back to its user.

PARAMÈTRES : 

